The same error occurs even with the simplified JSX! This confirms that the issue is not with the JSX content itself, but with the structural context before the return statement. The parser is in the wrong context and doesn't expect JSX.

This means there's definitely an unmatched opening brace, parenthesis, or some other structural issue somewhere before the return statement. Let me restore the JSX and focus on finding the real structural issue.
